  <div class="project-card">
    <div class="project-content">
      <span class="project-tag">Interactive Kiosk</span>
      <h3>Mack Truck Builder</h3>
      <p>A touch-screen kiosk built for museum floors — where real truck engineering becomes something kids and families can play with. Visitors configure every system and drive what they built. <strong>60+ unique combinations</strong>, a <strong>real-time physics game loop</strong>, and a <strong>live leaderboard</strong> — built for the <strong>Da Vinci Science Center</strong> in Allentown, PA.</p>
      <div class="stat-pills">
        <span class="stat-pill stat-pill--accent"><strong>5</strong> step guided experience</span>
        <span class="stat-pill"><strong>60+</strong> truck configurations</span>
        <span class="stat-pill"><strong>4</strong> truck classes</span>
        <span class="stat-pill"><strong>STEM</strong> content in 4 disciplines</span>
        <span class="stat-pill"><strong>60fps</strong> real-time physics</span>
        <span class="stat-pill"><strong>10,000+</strong> engaged kids</span>
      </div>
      <details class="project-expand">
        <summary>More about this project</summary>
        <div class="project-expand-content">
          <p>The experience moves Home → Factory → Customize → Drive → Leaderboard — five screens that walk visitors through the same decisions a real Mack engineer faces. Axle count. Wheelbase. Engine size. Fuel type. Tires. Aerodynamics. Accessories. Paint. Graphics.</p>
          <p>Every choice feeds a scoring formula that rewards fuel efficiency. So the best-engineered truck literally earns more time on the road. That's not a metaphor. That's the mechanic.</p>
          <p>The driving game is where STEM becomes visceral. Speed is tap-controlled — but each tap costs points. Kids feel the connection between smart engineering and real-world performance before they've ever heard the word "aerodynamics."</p>
          <p>Deployed at the <strong>Da Vinci Science Center</strong> in Allentown, PA — the same city where Mack Trucks has built since 1905.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
    <div class="project-gallery">
