  <div class="project-card project-card--dark">
    <div class="project-content">
      <span class="project-tag">Native iOS App</span>
      <h3>SoBo</h3>
      <p>SoBo is a friendship-safe lending app — a friendly middleman between the lend and the ask. Every loan gets its own negotiation thread, status tracking, and gentle nudge system. Lenders get their stuff back. Borrowers don't carry the guilt.</p>
      <p>Built for the generous ones who know the quiet cost of stuff that never comes back. Available on <strong>iOS & Google Play</strong> via <strong>React Native</strong> and <strong>Supabase</strong>.</p>
      <div class="stat-pills">
        <span class="stat-pill stat-pill--accent"><strong>iOS</strong> + <strong>Google Play</strong></span>
        <span class="stat-pill"><strong>5</strong> loan statuses tracked end-to-end</span>
        <span class="stat-pill"><strong>2-sided</strong> invite loop</span>
        <span class="stat-pill"><strong>AI humor</strong> baked into every nudge</span>
        <span class="stat-pill"><strong>Auto reminders</strong> sent for you</span>
        <span class="stat-pill stat-pill--accent"><strong>Discover</strong> nearby items</span>
      </div>
      <details class="project-expand">
        <summary>More about this project</summary>
        <div class="project-expand-content">
          <p>The origin is specific: a $450 trailer hitch lent to a friend, forgotten. Too awkward to bring up. SoBo was built from that moment — the invisible social tax that makes people quietly write off their stuff rather than deal with the ask.</p>
          <p>The app doesn't track items. It absorbs the awkwardness so the relationship stays intact. Both lenders and borrowers move through a <strong>5-status loan lifecycle</strong> — Pending, Active, Overdue, Returned, Canceled — with real-time conversation threads, before-and-after photos, and AI-timed nudges that land as friendly reminders, not debt collectors.</p>
          <p>The invite loop is structural. Every loan creates a frictionless entry point for the borrower, turning each lend into organic distribution with zero ad spend.</p>
          <p>A Discover screen lets neighbors browse publicly listed items nearby — a slow build toward community lending networks that scale beyond the friends-of-friends circle. The monetization arc follows: free tier to SoBo+ at $4.99/month to a full peer rental marketplace. One borrowed drill, a category-defining platform.</p>
          <p>Launching <strong>April 20, 2026</strong>. Pre-seed raise in progress.</p>
        </div>
